Description: Unique identifier for each loan or lease asset
Cash Flow Engine specific variable which triggers object type.
PossibleValues: (consumer_mortgage, consumer_auto, consumer_student, cosnumer_card, consumer_unsecured, commercial_mortgage, commercial_amortizing, commercial_bullet, commercial_revolver, commercial_abl_revolver, commercial_abl_fixed)

Description: Description of the loan product that is used to bucket for cash flow portfolios and stratification
Descriptor for specific credit and prepayment model to be used.  NOT CURRENTLY ACTIVE
Date on which the loan was originated and from which it starts accruing interest (generally the disbursal date)
Date on which the loan has its final maturity and all payments must be made
Date on which the tape as cut (also known as the as of date).  All current data is after this date
Original term in months beginning on the PMT_FIRSTPAY_DATE and ending on MATDATE
Age of the loan beginning on PMT_FIRSTPAY_DATE and ending on CUTOFFDATE
Remaining term of the loan calcualted as TERM_ORIG - TERM_AGE
Original outstanding principal balance of the loan on which interest accrues and which is due by MATDATE
NOTE: Consider ENUM
Type of documentation used at underwriting.  Referrs to income and employment verification if non-mortgage
PossibleValues: MTG: full; low; none | CONS: full; inc; emp; none |
